IAN WILLIAM JENKINS , 51, of Tilia Close, Scunthorpe, pleaded guilty to four offences of failing to comply with a notification requirement. He was committed to prison for 22 weeks, suspended for 12 months, and ordered to comply with a rehabilitation activity requirement. He was also ordered to pay a victim surcharge of £115 and costs of £85. 

 
RISHI LAL , 32, of Burke Street, Scunthorpe, pleaded guilty to harassment, assault and causing criminal damage. He was given a 12-month community order with a rehabilitation activity requirement and a 70-hour unpaid work requirement. He was also ordered to pay compensation of £300, a victim surcharge of £85 and costs of £85. 
 
